From: Hybrid Token-Efficient Routing Agent
Date: 2026
Subject: Per-task timeout + type-aware routing (non-blocking executor)

Fix a critical bug in the previous approach: ThreadPoolExecutor used as a
context manager calls shutdown(wait=True) on exit, which blocks until the
background thread finishes — defeating the timeout entirely.

New approach:
1. Persistent module-level ThreadPoolExecutor — never shut down.
2. Track _local_future; if a previous call is still in-flight (not done()),
   skip local inference to avoid concurrent llama.cpp access.
3. On timeout, just return None; abandoned thread runs to completion
   silently with its results discarded (zero wall-clock cost to caller).
4. Per-task-type timeouts via dict (math=90s, factual_qa=30s, others=45s).

